    text: "Every labelled patch panel, every colour-coded Cat6 run, and every crisp 4K comparison generates DMs from building managers whose own comms cupboards contain tangled BNC cables and flickering monitors."
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What Instagram account type do I need?",
    answer: "Use the app to switch to a Business or Creator profile — no cost and activates instantly. Security firms posting CCTV before-and-after comparisons, structured cabling close-ups, and 4K night footage samples attract exceptional engagement — property managers immediately recognise the upgrade their own grainy analogue systems need when they see crystal-clear number plates at midnight."
  },
  {
    question: "What security DMs arrive through Instagram?",
    answer: "Homeowners wanting cameras after porch theft or attempted break-ins. Shop owners needing CCTV evidence after shoplifting incidents. Facilities managers comparing your commercial installations with their own underperforming systems. Property developers studying your show home security packages. Pub landlords needing cameras after violence or anti-social behaviour. Each follower has pre-evaluated your NSI-approved standard."
  },
  {
    question: "How quickly does the AI respond to security DMs?",
    answer: "Every DM receives a response within seconds. Instagram's read indicator confirms your security firm actively monitors. A warehouse manager whose site was broken into last night — pallets of stock stolen, police saying existing cameras produced unusable footage — demands an immediate, knowledgeable reply from an NSI-approved installer, not an account showing last activity from three weeks earlier."
  },
  {
    question: "What do Instagram DMs cost for security contractors?",
    answer: `Instagram DMs are an add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month. A domestic CCTV and alarm installation generates £1,500 to £4,000. A commercial integrated security system generates £10,000 to £50,000. One facilities manager's twenty-four-camera IP upgrade — initiated by a DM after watching your veterinary hospital ColorVu reel — returns the annual channel investment from one project.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I reply to DMs myself?",
    answer: "Post one message in any thread and the AI withdraws permanently. Most security installers let the AI gather the initial scope — property type, existing security, crime trigger, camera count, alarm grade, and monitoring preference — then engage personally to discuss camera positions, zone configurations, and the survey date."
  },
  {
    question: "Is DM data from security queries private?",
    answer: "Instagram DMs — alarm fault photos, premises images, camera position queries, vulnerability descriptions, and sender contact information — are encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Nothing reaches competing security firms, equipment distributors, or third-party lead platforms."
