  accentWord="Security"
  subhead="Your latest reel is a forty-five-second split-screen comparison of a commercial CCTV upgrade at a car dealership in Witney. The left side: the old system — four grainy analogue cameras producing 352×288 resolution footage where number plates are unreadable beyond two metres and faces are pixelated blobs, fed through corroded BNC cables to a failing DVR with a three-day recording capacity. The right side: the new system — twelve Hikvision DS-2CD2T87G2-L ColorVu 4K cameras producing full-colour footage day and night without IR, with number plates legible at twenty-five metres, facial features identifiable at fifteen metres, and ANPR at both entrance and exit barriers capturing every vehicle registration. The NVR records at 4K for sixty days. The access control — Paxton Net2 proximity readers on the showroom entrance, the key safe room, and the workshop — shows each staff member's badge time on the audit trail. The final frame: a midnight screenshot showing a full-colour image of a vehicle and driver passing the ANPR camera, registration clearly readable, compared to the old system's grey blur at the same position. Nine thousand views. A fleet manager in Carterton DMs: 'Incredible difference. We run a commercial vehicle depot — forty-eight vans parked overnight in an open yard. We have eight old cameras but the footage is terrible — we had two catalytic converter thefts last month and the police said the camera quality was not sufficient for prosecution. We need what you showed — proper cameras that can actually identify people and read number plates at night. We also want an intruder alarm connected to monitoring covering the workshop and the fuel store. The yard is about 100 metres by 60 metres. Can you design a system and quote?' You are programming a Texecom panel. Without AI DMs, the fleet depot waits. With it, the AI confirms your commercial CCTV and ANPR capability, asks about the yard lighting and whether the perimeter is fenced, and captures: Carterton fleet depot 48 vans, 8 old cameras useless, 2 cat converter thefts last month, police said insufficient quality, 4K upgrade + ANPR, intruder alarm monitoring workshop + fuel store, yard 100m × 60m, day and night identification, quote."
  scenario="It is 4am on a Sunday. A letting agent DMs after a property emergency: 'Hi — we manage a block of sixty flats in Headington. Tonight a resident reported an intruder in the car park who was trying car door handles. The block has no CCTV at all — the previous management company never installed any. We need a comprehensive system urgently: CCTV covering the car park, all entrance lobbies, stairwells, bin stores, and the cycle shelter. Also need the old audio intercom at the main entrance replaced with a video intercom — flat residents cannot see who is buzzing. Access control on the underground car park entrance. Our management company budget for the upgrade has already been approved by the freeholder — we just need an NSI-approved firm to design, install, and maintain. Sixty flats, four storeys, two stairwells, underground car park, two lifts. Can you survey this week?' Without AI DMs, the sixty-flat block waits until Sunday afternoon. With AI DMs, the reply at 4:01am confirms your NSI approval and multi-site residential capability, asks about the existing network infrastructure and the car park lighting, and captures: Headington 60 flats 4 storeys 2 stairwells 2 lifts underground car park, intruder tonight car door handles, no existing CCTV, cameras car park + lobbies + stairwells + bin stores + cycle shelter, video intercom replacement, access control underground car park, freeholder approved budget, NSI approved, design + install + maintain, survey this week."
